> Maybe a comment could do the job ?

As you can see, there's already one. Is it helpful?

> we are using `c_str()' that returns an null terminated string

`c_str()` does return a null-terminated C string... but the `memcpy` is not copying it into the `sun_path`, due to `memcpy(address.sun_path, path_.c_str(), path_.size());` â€” `.size()` does not include the last null.

